  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Thank you for your comments and we are sorry to hear of the problems you encountered when seeking to park and drop off at Royal Oldham Hospital recently.
Unfortunately our parking is often extremely busy and we understand how frustrating this must be and so apologise for the inconvenience.
Whilst we continually review and invest in parking provision whenever possible, we are not able to provide an infinite number of parking spaces due to land, planning and funding constraints.  In order to counteract the often high demand for parking, plus with the commitment of the NHS to encourage active and sustainable lifestyles for all, we also seek to encourage staff in particular, plus patients and visitors where applicable, to make use of alternative travel choices to our hospital sites.  Our website does also include information on alternative travel methods to our hospital site, https://www.pat.nhs.uk/getting-here/the-royal-oldham-hospital.htm.
Finally, we are currently seeking additional options for better utilisation of on-site parking for patients and visitors including improved signage and off-site parking nearby to ease the parking situation; but these are subject to agreements with landowners and securing funding. 
Should you remain dissatisfied and wish to discuss your experience further, please contact the Patient Advice and Liaison Service (PALS) at your earliest opportunity on telephone 0161 604 5897, or email pals@pat.nhs.uk quoting that you have been advised to do so via NHS Website, and they will do their best to address your concerns

Kind regards
The Patient Experience Team
